snippet.textDisplay: Having watched and enjoyed bother shows I feel the need to point out something that they forgot. We've never actually seen all mights full power. When he punched numu into orbit he didn't just punch a thousand pounds of pure muscle. Numu was designed to beat all might. His body absorbed 99%of the force of all mights blows before it was to much. So we actually have to multiple the force  used to send numu to orbit by 99 and then multiply that total by sixty to find out how hard all might could have punched. I don't have the exact numbers but I'm pretty sure he'd be cracking planets in half. As we know that kind of power leads to similar speed. Allmights top speed should be way faster than lightning making him faster than might guy. It wouldn't be a fight untill the seventh gate but all might would still be holding back. Night guy would be able to match all might in every way though. It would come down to who has the more effective technique. So let's compare an f5 tornado to a blood dragon.
